{"lemma":"مُطَّرِدٍ","slug":"مُطَّرِدٍ","root":"ط.ر.د","root_slug":"ط-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26563","n26566","n26567","n26569"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%AF%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"steady, uninterrupted, consistent, regular, incessant","examples":[{"text":"أَفْعَالٌ مُطَّرِدَةٌ وَشَاذَّةٌ","english":"regular and irregular verbs"},{"text":"مُطَّرِد النَّسَق","english":"uniform"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb اِطَّرَدَ (iṭṭarada, “to be uninterrupted, to flow”)."},"ipa":["/mutˤ.tˤa.rid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26563","headword_ar":"مِطْرَدٌ","root":"Trd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A spear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because one hunts ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yTrd","text_ar":"يطرد"},{"kind":"text","text":") with it: (Msb:) or, (S, M, A, Mgh, L, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiraAdN","text_ar":"طِرَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K, [in my copy of the Mgh, app.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tar~aAd","text_ar":"طَرَّاد"},{"kind":"text","text":", its pl. being there plainly written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tar~AdAt","text_ar":"طَرّادات"},{"kind":"text","text":", though the sing. is doubtfully written, and it may be that Freytag, who mentions"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tar~aAdp","text_ar":"طَرَّادة"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"was led to do so from his finding"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiraAdaAt","text_ar":"طِرَادَات"},{"kind":"text","text":", which I believe to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiraAdN","text_ar":"طِرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tr~AdAt","text_ar":"طرّادات"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a short spear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, Mgh, L, K,) so called for the reason above mentioned, (Mgh,) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one hunts"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yTrd","text_ar":"يطرد"},{"kind":"text","text":"), or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one hunts wild animals;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a short hunting-spear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a short spear with which one thrusts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pierces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild animals,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild asses:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTaAridu","text_ar":"مَطَارِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) [And Freytag mentions"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTaAridu","text_ar":"مَطَارِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a pl. without sing., occurring in the Deewán of the Hudhalees, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Long arrows."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","M","A","Mgh","L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n26566","headword_ar":"مُطَرَّدٌ","root":"Trd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariydN","text_ar":"طَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tar~aAdN","text_ar":"طَرَّادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26567","headword_ar":"مُطَرِّدٌ","root":"Trd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Freytag, occurs in the Deewán of the Hudhalees, applied to a spear, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Altogether straight, so that the whole trembles:"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1840},{"kind":"text","text":"for that which is crooked does not. But this, if not a mistranscription, is app. used by poetic license, for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muT~aridN","text_ar":"مُطَّرِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26569","headword_ar":"مُطَّرَدٌ","root":"Trd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariydN","text_ar":"طَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}